    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-06-07T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-06-07T02:00:00-05:00" n="442"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d442">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00B/6–749: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hong Kong</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hopper</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hong Kong</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-06-07T16:00:00+09:00"
                            >June 7, 1949—4 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 7—7:41 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>311. … Source reports … that Chiao Mu<note n="93" xml:id="d442fn93">Chinese
                        Communist spokesman at Hong Kong.</note> now acting as informal unofficial
                    Consul [at] Hong Kong for Communists. Chiao performs such functions as clearing
                    travellers desiring go Shanghai and handling problems arising from foreign
                    shipping. In conversation with source June 4, Chiao indicated strong desire
                    Communists for US trade but stated if US adopted restrictive measures directed
                    at Communist government, Communist reaction would be swift and strong. Chiao
                    estimated Canton be taken by Communists at will and they would do so by July 1.
                    Chiao volunteered Hong Kong question can only be settled on highest level and
                    will be considered by Communists as integral factor in Communist–British
                    relations.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 311; repeated Shanghai 82, OffEmb Canton.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hopper</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
